# Project Architecture

## Folder structure

- `config/` — app-specific configuration (investment rates, targets, projections). Suffix: `.config.ts`
- `src/utils/` — pure, reusable functions (no React, no side effects). Suffix: `.util.ts`
- `src/hooks/` — custom React hooks grouped by logical domain. Suffix: `.hooks.ts`
- `src/contexts/` — React Context providers + consumer hooks. Suffix: `Context.tsx`
- `src/types/` — shared TypeScript interfaces and type definitions

## Components (Atomic Design)

- `atoms/` — smallest building blocks (RateSelector, SummaryCard, ThemeToggle)
- `molecules/` — compositions of atoms (PrognoseLineChart, SummaryCards, MobileDataCard)
- `organisms/` — full sections with business logic (AppBar, AppHeader, BottomNav)
- `pages/` — top-level page components (DashboardPage, InvestmentsPage, PensionPage, MonthlySavingsPage)

## Key rules

- No `.find()` or `.filter()` calls in components — extract to utils or hooks
- No prop drilling — use Context + custom hooks for shared state
- No magic numbers — use named constants from `config/investment.config.ts`
- Pages are lazy-loaded via `React.lazy()` with a `Suspense` fallback
